  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ngasso - Community Stabilization and Economic Recovery for Women in Lac Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through the creation of a women managed community garden with off grid and sustainable irrigation in Chad, this project aims to reduce the risk of gender-based violence towards women by increasing the availability of local economic opportunities for women. The main activities include: 1) the selection of women who benefit from the project and the creation of the group; 2) identification of cultivable space in coordination with local authorities; 3) provision of a borehole and installation of a solar water pump; 4) training on improved cultivation technics and solar pump maintenance; and 5) donation of seeds and tools for cultivation to the group. The creation of a community garden with solar powered pumps, tools, and furniture of seeds has been proven as an effective means of enhancing productivity even in soil without a high degree of fertility from experiences in other IOM Chad programs, and is a highly viable mean to contribute to community livelihoods under the management of women. IOM works in close collaboration with the local authorities and state specialists in the region including in the coordination of the location of the borehole, as well as its safety features and water quality.</narrative>
  </description>
